var statements=[{"text":"The procedure is mainly qualitative to start with, asking what is known of the processes, what records, instrumentation and monitoring are available, and how far they are compatible with the physical and temporal scope dictated by the purposes and objectives.","position":1,"link":"https://hypothes.is/a/jFet6qj0EemvjlOSHfMLaw","annotation":"Subject: specification of data and other prior knowledge \nPredicate: has subtask","subject":"specification of data and other prior knowledge","predicate":"has subtask","object":"The procedure is mainly qualitative to start with, asking what is known of the processes, what records, instrumentation and monitoring are available, and how far they are compatible with the physical and temporal scope dictated by the purposes and objectives."},{"text":"However, it becomes quantitative as soon as we have to decide what to include and what can be simplified or neglected. What variables are to be included, in how much detail? Once the outputs are selected, a rough assessment is needed of which drivers they are sensitive to and what internal processes influence the relations between the drivers and outputs; this will usually be partly a quantitative assessment.","position":2,"link":"https://hypothes.is/a/vtFNlKj0EemZeXsCJ_WILA","annotation":"Subject: specification of data and other prior knowledge\nPredicate: has subtask","subject":"specification of data and other prior knowledge","predicate":"has subtask","object":"However, it becomes quantitative as soon as we have to decide what to include and what can be simplified or neglected. What variables are to be included, in how much detail? Once the outputs are selected, a rough assessment is needed of which drivers they are sensitive to and what internal processes influence the relations between the drivers and outputs; this will usually be partly a quantitative assessment."},{"text":"3.3. Conceptualisation of the system, specification of data and other prior knowledge","position":3,"link":"https://hypothes.is/a/AKBxoKhaEemgaZfzpKZnCQ","annotation":"Subject: conceptualisation\nPredicate: has subtask\nObject: conceptualisation of the system\nObject: specification of data and other prior knowledge\n\nSubject: conceptualisation of the system\nPredicate: redirect to\nObject: system conceptualisation","subject":"conceptualisation","predicate":"has subtask","object":"specification of data and other prior knowledge"},{"text":"3.3. Conceptualisation of the system, specification of data and other prior knowledge","position":3,"link":"https://hypothes.is/a/AKBxoKhaEemgaZfzpKZnCQ","annotation":"Subject: conceptualisation\nPredicate: has subtask\nObject: conceptualisation of the system\nObject: specification of data and other prior knowledge\n\nSubject: conceptualisation of the system\nPredicate: redirect to\nObject: system conceptualisation","subject":"conceptualisation","predicate":"has subtask","object":"system conceptualisation"},{"text":"It includes observational data and their properties (including error characteristics), structural information (e.g. coupling or independence, additivity of effects or interaction, existence of feedbacks), the nature of processes (e.g. stationarity, correlations, directionality of flows, conservation laws, switching between modes), the extent and nature of spatio-temporal forcing, and parameter values and their uncertainties.","position":4,"link":"https://hypothes.is/a/ZMDEsqhSEemC6pNwVno9fg","annotation":"Subject: specification of data and other prior knowledge\nPredicate: uses\nObject: prior knowledge\n\nSubject: prior knowledge\nPredicate: has subclass","subject":"specification of data and other prior knowledge","predicate":"uses","object":"prior knowledge"},{"text":"“Prior knowledge” can be genuinely known in advance, found from experiments or analyses performed as part of model development, or assumed, with reservations, on the basis of experience.","position":5,"link":"https://hypothes.is/a/XpS5XqhSEem2oy-lmKJAzw","annotation":"Subject: prior knowledge\nPredicate: has subclass","subject":"prior knowledge","predicate":"has subclass","object":"“Prior knowledge” can be genuinely known in advance, found from experiments or analyses performed as part of model development, or assumed, with reservations, on the basis of experience."},{"text":"Quantitative information on uncertain parameters and errors may consist of point estimates and variances or covariances, bounds (ranges) or, if you are lucky, probability distributions.","position":6,"link":"https://hypothes.is/a/bG7SJqhSEemXx59ChyNrnw","annotation":"Subject: prior knowledge\nPredicate: has subclass\nObject: quantitative prior knowledge\n\nSubject: quantitative prior knowledge\nPredicate: has subclass","subject":"prior knowledge","predicate":"has subclass","object":"quantitative prior knowledge"},{"text":"Ill-chosen intervals can destroy the validity of the model, but once recognized can be amended as part of the learning process.","position":7,"link":"https://hypothes.is/a/Oxp8cKhSEem3zItFXJNRzg","annotation":"Subject: definition of model scale and resolution\nPredicate: problem","subject":"definition of model scale and resolution","predicate":"problem","object":"Ill-chosen intervals can destroy the validity of the model, but once recognized can be amended as part of the learning process."},{"text":"Such assessment takes considerable effort and insight into the processes operating in the system, so it is often given too little attention. Too often sampling intervals in time and space are chosen by guesswork or simply because data are available at those intervals","position":8,"link":"https://hypothes.is/a/NsW5-qhSEemlbnPw1X4U5A","annotation":"Subject: quantitative assessment of effect of model scale and resolution\nPredicate: problem","subject":"quantitative assessment of effect of model scale and resolution","predicate":"problem","object":"Such assessment takes considerable effort and insight into the processes operating in the system, so it is often given too little attention. Too often sampling intervals in time and space are chosen by guesswork or simply because data are available at those intervals"},{"text":"The only way to ensure that these requirements are met is by a careful quantitative assessment.","position":9,"link":"https://hypothes.is/a/JtTYgqhSEem2oXfdRlWm0g","annotation":"Subject: definition of model scale and resolution\nPredicate: has subtask\nObject: quantitative assessment of effect of model scale and resolution\n","subject":"definition of model scale and resolution","predicate":"has subtask","object":"quantitative assessment of effect of model scale and resolution"},{"text":"However, the next step is to follow up the implications: the internal resolution of the model must be sufficient to produce outputs at the required resolution, and the time and spatial intervals throughout the model must be compatible with the range of rates of change of the variables.","position":10,"link":"https://hypothes.is/a/IiJQdqhSEemXaCMJzIsKmw","annotation":"Subject: conceptualisation\nPredicate: has subtask\nObject: definition of model scale and resolution\n\nSubject: definition of model scale and resolution\nPredicate: criteria","subject":"conceptualisation","predicate":"has subtask","object":"definition of model scale and resolution"},{"text":"The first part of this step is just to state what degree of detail is needed in the outputs.","position":11,"link":"https://hypothes.is/a/APjqfKhSEemaB1PUY9QyOQ","annotation":"Subject: conceptualisation\nPredicate: has subtask\nObject: state degree of detail needed in outputs","subject":"conceptualisation","predicate":"has subtask","object":"state degree of detail needed in outputs"},{"text":"This is not trivial. Few models are flexible enough to respond to these evolving needs, which are commonly passed off by modellers as due to the client “not thinking their problem through properly at the beginning.”","position":12,"link":"https://hypothes.is/a/-Amo3qhREemYAScWMGAKiw","annotation":"Subject: modifying conceptualisation as experience grows\nPredicate: problem","subject":"modifying conceptualisation as experience grows","predicate":"problem","object":"This is not trivial. Few models are flexible enough to respond to these evolving needs, which are commonly passed off by modellers as due to the client “not thinking their problem through properly at the beginning.”"},{"text":"The degree of aggregation and the spatio-temporal resolution (intervals and accuracy) of the outputs also have to be chosen but, as for all these decisions, the choices may have to be revised as experience grows. The time-step and the bounds of what is to be modelled may have to be modified part way through an application, perhaps more than once.","position":13,"link":"https://hypothes.is/a/1psfFqhREemlavMdmme7tw","annotation":"Subject: conceptualisation\nPredicate: has subtask\nObject: Choose degree of aggregation and spatio-temporal resolution (intervals and accuracy)\nObjet: modifying conceptualisation as experience grows","subject":"conceptualisation","predicate":"has subtask","object":"Choose degree of aggregation and spatio-temporal resolution (intervals and accuracy)"},{"text":"This third step defines the data, prior knowledge and assumptions about processes. ","position":14,"link":"https://hypothes.is/a/jTUgiKhREem0eSOlDtEdBw","annotation":"Subject: conceptualisation\nPredicate: has subtask\nObject: specification of data and other prior knowledge\n\nSubject: specification of data and other prior knowledge\nPredicate: synonym\nObject: define the data, prior knowledge and assumptions about processes","subject":"specification of data and other prior knowledge","predicate":"synonym","object":"define the data, prior knowledge and assumptions about processes"},{"text":"This third step defines the data, prior knowledge and assumptions about processes. ","position":14,"link":"https://hypothes.is/a/jTUgiKhREem0eSOlDtEdBw","annotation":"Subject: conceptualisation\nPredicate: has subtask\nObject: specification of data and other prior knowledge\n\nSubject: specification of data and other prior knowledge\nPredicate: synonym\nObject: define the data, prior knowledge and assumptions about processes","subject":"conceptualisation","predicate":"has subtask","object":"specification of data and other prior knowledge"},{"text":"The conceptualisation step is important even if a model is not designed from scratch because time and money (as well as the clients' beliefs) restrict one to using a ‘canned’ model. Conceptualisation exposes the weaknesses of the canned approach and perhaps ways to mitigate them.","position":15,"link":"https://hypothes.is/a/byi7mqhREemt4cNh9YjyUA","annotation":"Subject: conceptualisation\nPredicate: when to use","subject":"conceptualisation","predicate":"when to use","object":"The conceptualisation step is important even if a model is not designed from scratch because time and money (as well as the clients' beliefs) restrict one to using a ‘canned’ model. Conceptualisation exposes the weaknesses of the canned approach and perhaps ways to mitigate them."},{"text":"A tentative initial conceptualisation and a visualisation such as a block diagram may be a great help in showing what else must be found out about the system.","position":16,"link":"https://hypothes.is/a/W7P38KhREemacWddlk95CA","annotation":"Subject: tentative conceptualisation\nPredicate: use\nObject: $q","subject":"tentative conceptualisation","predicate":"use","object":"A tentative initial conceptualisation and a visualisation such as a block diagram may be a great help in showing what else must be found out about the system."},{"text":"Initially the conceptualisation may be rudimentary, with details postponed until the results of knowledge elicitation and data analysis can be exploited.","position":17,"link":"https://hypothes.is/a/VisUYqhREemC4_ucq_Smyg","annotation":"Subject: conceptualisation of system\nPredicate: redirect to\nObject: system conceptualisation\n\nSubject: system conceptualisation\nPredicate: has subtask\nObject: tentative conceptualisation\n\nSubject: tentative conceptualisation\nPredicate: description\nObject: $q\n","subject":"tentative conceptualisation","predicate":"description","object":"Initially the conceptualisation may be rudimentary, with details postponed until the results of knowledge elicitation and data analysis can be exploited."},{"text":"Initially the conceptualisation may be rudimentary, with details postponed until the results of knowledge elicitation and data analysis can be exploited.","position":17,"link":"https://hypothes.is/a/VisUYqhREemC4_ucq_Smyg","annotation":"Subject: conceptualisation of system\nPredicate: redirect to\nObject: system conceptualisation\n\nSubject: system conceptualisation\nPredicate: has subtask\nObject: tentative conceptualisation\n\nSubject: tentative conceptualisation\nPredicate: description\nObject: $q\n","subject":"system conceptualisation","predicate":"has subtask","object":"tentative conceptualisation"},{"text":"It might employ aids to thinking such as an influence diagram, linguistic model, block diagram or bond graph (Gawthrop and Smith, 1996, Wellstead, 1979), showing how model drivers are linked to internal (state) variables and outputs (observed responses).","position":18,"link":"https://hypothes.is/a/QnLb2qhREemTmMMyWK7bfA","annotation":"Subject: conceptualisation of system\nPredicate: can use\nObject: system conceptualisation tools\n\nSubject: system conceptualisation tools\nObject: aids to thinking showing how model drivers are linked to internal (state) variables and outputs (observed responses)\nObject: influence diagrams\nObject: linguistic model\nObject: block diagram\nObject: bond graph\n\nSubject: system conceptualisation tools\nPredicate: reference\nObject: Gawthrop and Smith, 1996\nObject: Wellstead, 1979","subject":"system conceptualisation tools","predicate":"reference","object":"W